---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="The Studio"
  eyebrow="About"
  description="Self Esteem is a small editorial studio publishing essays on attention, motivation, and the work of being a person in 2026."
>
  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      We are a small, distributed group of writers and editors. We publish slowly — usually one
      essay a month, occasionally a longer issue. We do not chase breaking news. We are interested
      in what survives the silence after.
    </p>

    <h2>What we publish</h2>
    <p>
      Long-form essays, occasional interviews, and reading lists. Most issues sit on a single
      question and turn it over for ten or twelve pages. Nothing is sponsored. Nothing is paywalled.
    </p>

    <h2>People</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Richard Carnation</strong> — editor, essays on attention.</li>
      <li><strong>Scarlett Witch</strong> — writer, mental health and care.</li>
      <li><strong>Tom Hiddleston</strong> — writer, love and vulnerability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>
    <p>
      Reach us via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. We read everything and reply to most
      things.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
